*   [Fully protected](/Category:Wikipedia_fully_protected_redirects): This designation indicates that the redirect you've stumbled upon originates from a title that has been deemed sufficiently important—or perhaps sufficiently contentious—to warrant complete protection from editing. Such safeguards are typically put in place by an administrator, acting as a digital bouncer, or because the page has been included on the [Cascade-protected list](/Wikipedia:Cascade-protected_items/content). The reasons for this level of protection can vary, ranging from preventing disruptive edits to preserving the integrity of high-traffic or highly visible pages. It’s a measure designed to ensure stability, or at least, to prevent utter chaos, which, frankly, is often a losing battle.

